  "prompt": "What are the advantages and disadvantages of having one's mother tongue as the medium of instruction during primary education in India?",
  "response": "Here's a balanced analysis of using mother tongue as the medium of instruction during primary education in India:\n\nAdvantages:\n1. Cognitive Development\n- Better comprehension and learning\n- Easier conceptual understanding\n- Enhanced critical thinking skills\n- Reduced cognitive load\n\n2. Linguistic and Cultural Preservation\n- Strengthens cultural identity\n- Promotes linguistic diversity\n- Maintains connection with native language\n- Prevents language erosion\n\n3. Psychological Benefits\n- Increased confidence\n- Reduced learning anxiety\n- More comfortable learning environment\n- Better emotional connection to education\n\n4. Academic Performance\n- Higher retention of knowledge\n- Faster learning\n- More natural learning process\n- Improved communication skills\n\nDisadvantages:\n1. Limited Mobility\n- Challenges in inter-state education\n- Reduced employability\n- Difficulty accessing national/global opportunities\n\n2. Language Constraints\n- Limited scientific/technical terminology\n- Potential knowledge gaps\n- Complexity in translating advanced concepts\n\n3. Multilingual Challenges\n- India's linguistic diversity complicates implementation\n- Requires significant resource investment\n- Potential administrative complexities\n\n4. English Language Proficiency\n- Reduced exposure to English\n- Potential competitive disadvantage\n- Limited international communication skills\n\nBalanced implementation requires careful considerations of local contexts and long-term educational goals.",
